## Common Parameters

### Log Path Handling

All commands support `--log <path>` with intelligent path resolution:

| Input | Resolved Path | Example |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| Filename only | `test-logs/<filename>` | `tests.log` ŌåÆ `test-logs/tests.log` |
| Relative path | `test-logs/<path>` | `api/tests.log` ŌåÆ `test-logs/api/tests.log` |
| Absolute path | Used as-is | `/tmp/tests.log` ŌåÆ `/tmp/tests.log` |

**Note**: `test-logs/` is already in `.gitignore`

### HTML Report Opening

Coverage commands support `--open` flag to automatically open HTML reports in the default browser:
- **macOS**: Uses `open` command
- **Linux**: Uses `xdg-open` command

